    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Eleven factors were fully assessed; one factor (Test conditions) achieved level 1 against a required level 2, which is an acknowledged limitation of the standardized ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol and is accepted given the regulatory precedent for this test method. Two factors (Numerical solver error; Use error) were not-assessed, with the team noting these were beyond the scope of the current submission. The output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; per-specimen errors < 10%) satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds. The overall credibility package is accepted at Medium assurance level for the stated COU, with the not-assessed factors noted as areas for improvement in subsequent submissions.",
